betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§7§oME storage busses use one channel to connect to an inventory. Any items contained in the inventory will become part of the network, and can be seen in the terminals.

Extract only mode makes it so you can see the storage in your terminal, but the network will not store new items into the storage.

Insert only mode makes it so you will not be able to see the storage in your terminal, but it will force the network to move items into the storage.
